How much has he won?

511
00:22:07.960 --> 00:22:09.562
It's over 200.000. Sir.

512
00:22:09.696 --> 00:22:11.097
SID:
Having got his attention.

513
00:22:11.498 --> 00:22:13.065
he's going to be looking
at me very dubiously.

514
00:22:13.199 --> 00:22:14.701
So. I'll need to convince him
that I have

515
00:22:14.834 --> 00:22:16.335
no kind of hidden agenda.

516
00:22:16.836 --> 00:22:18.705
Naturally. being the host
and rather paranoid.

517
00:22:18.838 --> 00:22:20.640
he's going to assume that
I'm a grifter and he's the mark.

518
00:22:20.773 --> 00:22:22.341
So. he'll challenge me.

519
00:22:22.542 --> 00:22:24.176
- May I?
- Please.

520
00:22:25.845 --> 00:22:27.814
What do you say.
5.000 a point?

521
00:22:28.881 --> 00:22:29.982
Sure.

522
00:22:30.483 --> 00:22:31.651
- (dice rolling)
- (suspenseful music)

523
00:22:31.784 --> 00:22:32.952
SID: Using the loaded dice.

524
00:22:33.319 --> 00:22:34.654
I'll continue
my winning streak.

525
00:22:34.854 --> 00:22:36.823
Simultaneously.
I will refuse payment.

526
00:22:37.657 --> 00:22:39.459
He will insist on paying me.

527
00:22:39.892 --> 00:22:41.728
I make a point
of paying my debts.

528
00:22:42.128 --> 00:22:43.896
SID: But here's where
I make my final move.

529
00:22:44.030 --> 00:22:47.033
You can repay me
by giving me a rematch.

530
00:22:47.366 --> 00:22:48.501
but with a gentleman's bet

531
00:22:48.635 --> 00:22:49.636
and only for $10.

532
00:22:50.069 --> 00:22:51.170
RACHEL: You will lose.

533
00:22:51.303 --> 00:22:52.505
And as a token of a payment.

534
00:22:52.639 --> 00:22:54.373
you will offer him a gift.

535
00:22:54.741 --> 00:22:57.710
It just happens that that gift
is a statue he covets.

536
00:22:57.844 --> 00:22:59.712
Open exhibit B.

537
00:23:00.012 --> 00:23:01.748
- (clicking. sliding)
- (suspenseful music)

538
00:23:01.881 --> 00:23:03.716
In scurries the Trojan rat.

539
00:23:05.317 --> 00:23:07.520
It seems luck has gone my way.

540
00:23:07.754 --> 00:23:08.855
Well played.

541
00:23:08.988 --> 00:23:11.624
Er. rather embarrassingly.

542
00:23:11.758 --> 00:23:13.826
I don't carry that sort of cash.

543
00:23:14.193 --> 00:23:17.096
If you'll allow me. I'll just
pop something in the post?

544
00:23:17.564 --> 00:23:19.799
RACHEL NARRATING: People are not
suspicious of those that give.

545
00:23:19.932 --> 00:23:21.434
Only those that take.

546
00:23:21.568 --> 00:23:24.804
Sir. a gift has arrived
from Mr. Kershner.

547
00:23:24.937 --> 00:23:27.373
RACHEL: Wolfgang's office
is a Faraday cage.

548
00:23:27.507 --> 00:23:30.276
an impenetrable firewall
preventing anyone or anything

549
00:23:30.443 --> 00:23:31.978
from accessing his data.

550
00:23:32.244 --> 00:23:34.547
However. once you're inside
of said cage

551
00:23:34.714 --> 00:23:36.483
and within 12 feet
of his computer.

552
00:23:36.849 --> 00:23:37.984
we're in his world.

553
00:23:38.117 --> 00:23:39.619
Our statue is a bug.

554
00:23:39.752 --> 00:23:41.988
a camera
and a tempest attack device.

555
00:23:42.121 --> 00:23:43.623
We can start to put names
to companies

556
00:23:43.756 --> 00:23:45.558
and untangle his financial web.

557
00:23:45.958 --> 00:23:48.628
Bob's your uncle.
Fanny's your aunt. We're in.

558
00:23:48.895 --> 00:23:50.296
RACHEL: Now. I'm inside
Wolfgang's world.

559
00:23:50.463 --> 00:23:52.565
we can start to peel back
the onion.

560
00:23:53.232 --> 00:23:54.934
Once I have the legal traction
to freeze some more

561
00:23:55.067 --> 00:23:56.636
of his hidden assets...

562
00:23:56.903 --> 00:23:59.005
Oh. Wolfgang. I've got you now.

563
00:23:59.138 --> 00:24:01.173
...this will accelerate
a desire to reach a deal.

564
00:24:01.307 --> 00:24:02.742
The court approves
the application

565
00:24:02.875 --> 00:24:04.711
to seek international
attachment orders.

566
00:24:04.877 --> 00:24:06.445
Objection. Your Honor!

567
00:24:06.613 --> 00:24:07.780
Overruled!

568
00:24:08.214 --> 00:24:09.315
- (gavel bangs)
- Thank you. Your Honor.

569
00:24:12.284 --> 00:24:13.686
- She's a monster.
- (phone ringing)

570
00:24:13.820 --> 00:24:15.321
RACHEL NARRATING:
However. in order to get

571
00:24:15.454 --> 00:24:17.123
the unpalatable deal
that I want.

572
00:24:17.256 --> 00:24:18.925
I will need to look Salazar
in the eye.

573
00:24:19.058 --> 00:24:19.926
HOROWITZ: Hello?

574
00:24:20.392 --> 00:24:21.360
Hello?

575
00:24:21.494 --> 00:24:22.461
Oh. Mr. Horowitz.

576
00:24:22.629 --> 00:24:24.462
how lovely to hear from you.

577
00:24:24.463 --> 00:24:25.431
Okay. sweetheart.

578
00:24:26.799 --> 00:24:28.701
200. That's it.

579
00:24:28.835 --> 00:24:31.170
Has anyone ever told you
you have a wonderful timbre

580
00:24:31.303 --> 00:24:32.404
to your voice.

581
00:24:33.005 --> 00:24:34.440
I'm trying to place it.

582
00:24:34.574 --> 00:24:35.441
That's funny?

583
00:24:35.642 --> 00:24:36.676
200 is funny.

584
00:24:36.809 --> 00:24:38.444
- (snaps fingers)
- I got it.

585
00:24:38.645 --> 00:24:41.213
From the 1950s hit
The African Queen

586
00:24:41.347 --> 00:24:43.850
starring Katherine Hepburn
and Humphrey Bogart.

587
00:24:44.016 --> 00:24:45.985
You sound just like
Katherine Hepburn.

588
00:24:46.619 --> 00:24:47.486
Okay.

589
00:24:47.620 --> 00:24:48.855
(water lapping)

590
00:24:49.822 --> 00:24:50.857
300.

591
00:24:51.090 --> 00:24:52.625
I wanna sit down with Salazar.

592
00:24:52.759 --> 00:24:55.094
Since I can't talk to you.
I wanna talk to him.

593
00:24:55.361 --> 00:24:58.230
- (dial tone)
- What?! You f... You fu...

594
00:24:58.364 --> 00:25:00.633
You fucking cu...

595
00:25:00.767 --> 00:25:02.234
Salam Alaikum.

596
00:25:02.368 --> 00:25:03.703
RACHEL:
Salazar doesn't know it yet.

597
00:25:03.836 --> 00:25:05.504
but he's going to agree
to a meeting.

598
00:25:05.638 --> 00:25:07.139
It's gonna happen on the island.

599
00:25:07.373 --> 00:25:09.308
That's the only place
he'll feel safe.

600
00:25:09.441 --> 00:25:12.378
It's just a question of when.
but there's still plenty of time

601
00:25:12.545 --> 00:25:14.180
for you and your boys to put
in the infrastructure

602
00:25:14.313 --> 00:25:15.514
and prepare for the worst.

603
00:25:15.648 --> 00:25:16.716
Bronco?

604
00:25:17.349 --> 00:25:18.718
I'm sure you've had
a sniff around.

605
00:25:19.118 --> 00:25:20.152
How do we feel about that?

606
00:25:20.319 --> 00:25:21.554
I think we feel okay.

607
00:25:21.954 --> 00:25:23.022
Okay.

608
00:25:23.155 --> 00:25:24.023
Better get more boots then.

609
00:25:24.190 --> 00:25:26.125
(dramatic music)

610
00:25:30.129 --> 00:25:31.097
BRONCO: Phase two.

611
00:25:31.297 --> 00:25:32.765
Planning and preparation.

612
00:25:33.065 --> 00:25:34.834
(boat motor humming)

613
00:25:39.839 --> 00:25:41.140
Mr. Beauregard.

614
00:25:42.074 --> 00:25:43.610
Buenos días. Captain Sensible.

615
00:25:43.810 --> 00:25:44.777
Love the shirt.

616
00:25:45.044 --> 00:25:45.812
It's silk.

617
00:25:46.713 --> 00:25:47.513
Like my sheets.

618
00:25:48.648 --> 00:25:49.616
Course it is.

619
00:25:49.882 --> 00:25:51.350
RACHEL: My insurance policy

620
00:25:51.483 --> 00:25:52.118
will need to consist
of a full team.

621
00:25:52.251 --> 00:25:53.886
Baker...

622
00:25:54.320 --> 00:25:55.321
RACHEL: Baker will be in charge
of explosives

623
00:25:55.487 --> 00:25:56.689
and munitions.

624
00:25:57.423 --> 00:26:00.459
Moreno is a wheel man in charge
of on-ground transport.

625
00:26:00.827 --> 00:26:04.096
Dunne is in charge of
aviation... and cynicism.

626
00:26:04.330 --> 00:26:05.564
This is Gucci.

627
00:26:05.698 --> 00:26:06.532
He's in charge of tech.

628
00:26:09.736 --> 00:26:10.937
I just told you.

629
00:26:11.070 --> 00:26:12.772
- It's silk.
- (bag clunks)

630
00:26:12.905 --> 00:26:14.173
RACHEL: Their principal agenda

631
00:26:14.440 --> 00:26:15.942
will be getting me
off the island

632
00:26:16.075 --> 00:26:17.343
and should I need
to leave quickly.

633
00:26:17.509 --> 00:26:19.612
they'll need a full chest
of toys.

634
00:26:19.746 --> 00:26:21.848
Indigenous ambulance.
40.000 on the clock.

635
00:26:22.014 --> 00:26:25.384
full tank of laughing gas
and four brand new boots.

636
00:26:25.752 --> 00:26:27.453
- Baker. door.
- (door clanks open)

637
00:26:29.956 --> 00:26:31.357
Abracadabra.

638
00:26:31.490 --> 00:26:33.225
Say hello to Javier.

639
00:26:33.359 --> 00:26:35.828
- GROUP: Hello. Javier.
- Hola. chicos.

640
00:26:35.962 --> 00:26:38.731
He's been a very clever boy
and got the full shopping list.

641
00:26:38.931 --> 00:26:42.935
Two canoes. four oars.
two emergency outboards.

642
00:26:43.069 --> 00:26:47.439
Late 2010 coche.
upgraded with an LS3 V8.

643
00:26:47.740 --> 00:26:50.009
Three KTM 450s.

644
00:26:50.142 --> 00:26:53.379
125 scooter for eggs
and fresh milk.

645
00:26:53.579 --> 00:26:57.917
Two Polaris Razors with 190hp
and plenty of torque.

646
00:26:58.985 --> 00:27:00.319
And Teddy for fishing.

647
00:27:00.586 --> 00:27:02.955
We've got a full set
of knives and forks.

648
00:27:03.089 --> 00:27:04.023
We've got your reach out
and touch me

649
00:27:04.156 --> 00:27:05.424
for the long range slot.

650
00:27:05.658 --> 00:27:08.260
Noise makers. cloudies. blinders.

651
00:27:08.394 --> 00:27:11.764
We've got 9-mils and 45s
avec hush puppies.

652
00:27:12.131 --> 00:27:14.667
Gucci AR with a 203
grenade launcher.

653
00:27:14.967 --> 00:27:17.670
Brand new boom stick
with 40-mil butt plugs.

654
00:27:17.804 --> 00:27:18.905
Top cigars
for the Charlie Gs

655
00:27:19.071 --> 00:27:20.172
for ground to air.

656
00:27:20.306 --> 00:27:21.607
And finally...

657
00:27:22.141 --> 00:27:25.211
24 ice cold
cervezas.

658
00:27:25.511 --> 00:27:26.813
Please drink responsibly.

659
00:27:27.513 --> 00:27:28.647
BRONCO: Alright ladies.
don't get excited

660
00:27:28.781 --> 00:27:29.716
about our accommodation.

661
00:27:29.849 --> 00:27:31.050
It's not the Savoy.

662
00:27:31.450 --> 00:27:32.785
We're hidden in
the most remote part

663
00:27:32.952 --> 00:27:34.353
of Salazar's Island.

664
00:27:34.787 --> 00:27:36.789
We chose this safe house
due to its proximity

665
00:27:36.923 --> 00:27:40.559
to all three extraction points
and its historical tunnels.

666
00:27:40.693 --> 00:27:42.628
should we need to get
Rachel out discreetly.

667
00:27:42.762 --> 00:27:46.098
Rachel is only ever going to be
in one of two places.

668
00:27:46.365 --> 00:27:47.666
Either here at the villa.

669
00:27:47.934 --> 00:27:49.301
or at Salazar's hotel.

670
00:27:49.668 --> 00:27:51.804
He lives in the penthouse suite

671
00:27:51.971 --> 00:27:53.405
which is where they will meet.

672
00:27:53.639 --> 00:27:55.674
If things get exciting.

673
00:27:55.808 --> 00:27:56.743
we extract Mum.

674
00:27:56.876 --> 00:27:58.044
assess the threat level.

675
00:27:58.210 --> 00:27:59.478
bring her back to the villa

676
00:27:59.712 --> 00:28:00.913
and get her off the island.

677
00:28:01.047 --> 00:28:02.715
Three extraction points.

678
00:28:03.115 --> 00:28:04.516
BRONCO: If we need to move
Rachel from the hotel.

679
00:28:04.650 --> 00:28:06.552
we take the east evac route.

680
00:28:06.786 --> 00:28:09.088
We'll take the SUVs through the
town through the storm drains

681
00:28:09.221 --> 00:28:10.689
to two awaiting RIBs.

682
00:28:10.957 --> 00:28:12.759
If we need to extract her
from the villa.

683
00:28:12.892 --> 00:28:14.693
we go from an airfield
on the north of the island.

684
00:28:14.827 --> 00:28:16.162
Jets and helicopters
are a no-go

685
00:28:16.295 --> 00:28:18.330
because Salazar controls
the skies.

686
00:28:18.497 --> 00:28:20.199
That's why we came here
by boat.

687
00:28:20.332 --> 00:28:22.001
We have
two gyrocopters waiting.

688
00:28:22.134 --> 00:28:23.269
They'll go undetected.

689
00:28:23.736 --> 00:28:25.604
The west evac
is our last resort.

690
00:28:25.738 --> 00:28:28.174
There's no other way
off the island.

691
00:28:28.307 --> 00:28:31.110
Each route has its own
challenges but we need to reach

692
00:28:31.243 --> 00:28:33.846
these points as quickly
and efficiently as possible.

693
00:28:34.380 --> 00:28:36.048
We're gonna be ready
for any eventuality

694
00:28:36.182 --> 00:28:37.483
and practice until
we get it right.

695
00:28:37.649 --> 00:28:41.353
But this is Salazar's Island.

696
00:28:41.487 --> 00:28:43.222
The police are on payroll

697
00:28:43.555 --> 00:28:46.658
and he has a reasonably
experienced private army.

698
00:28:46.893 --> 00:28:48.828
- How many?
- Best guess. 50.

699
00:28:49.361 --> 00:28:51.864
- What's that all about?
- Considering his activities.

700
00:28:52.064 --> 00:28:54.433
he takes some comfort
from having a small militia.

701
00:28:54.566 --> 00:28:56.068
BRONCO: The police station
is an issue.

702
00:28:56.202 --> 00:28:57.703
If anyone ends up inside.
we need to know

703
00:28:57.837 --> 00:28:58.704
how to get 'em out.

704
00:28:58.838 --> 00:28:59.872
Where do you wanna start?

705
00:29:00.039 --> 00:29:01.740
Well. first we recce the routes

706
00:29:01.874 --> 00:29:03.609
and then we go look at the hotel
and the police station.

707
00:29:03.742 --> 00:29:04.743
We'll split up.

708
00:29:04.877 --> 00:29:06.012
Gucci. Dunne and Baker.

709
00:29:06.178 --> 00:29:07.780
you recce the north evac point

710
00:29:07.914 --> 00:29:09.548
and log a flight time
to the mainland.

711
00:29:09.681 --> 00:29:13.152
Bronco. Moreno and yours truly.

712
00:29:13.719 --> 00:29:16.155
We'll recce the fastest route
from Salazar's penthouse

713
00:29:16.755 --> 00:29:19.524
through the city
to the east evac point.

714
00:29:19.525 --> 00:29:21.227
(horns blaring)

715
00:29:22.594 --> 00:29:24.663
Hey. Captain Sensible.
can you. er.

716
00:29:24.797 --> 00:29:26.132
can you just slow down
a little bit?

717
00:29:26.265 --> 00:29:27.233
You're starting
to make me nervous.

718
00:29:29.568 --> 00:29:31.037
Time really does stand still...

719
00:29:32.071 --> 00:29:33.239
when I'm with you.

720
00:29:33.372 --> 00:29:34.406
Dunno what you're
so grumpy about.

721
00:29:34.540 --> 00:29:35.741
You planned the route.

722
00:29:35.875 --> 00:29:37.643
- (engine humming)
- (horns blaring)

723
00:29:38.811 --> 00:29:41.814
If we're not careful.
your dad's gonna blow our cover.

724
00:29:41.981 --> 00:29:43.850
(window squeaking)

725
00:29:44.383 --> 00:29:46.952
- Okay. Thank you.
- Okay.

726
00:29:46.953 --> 00:29:48.587
Tell your dad not
to spend it all at once.

727
00:29:48.821 --> 00:29:50.789
(motorbike revving)

728
00:29:51.090 --> 00:29:52.925
(motorbikes revving)

729
00:29:53.059 --> 00:29:54.660
Are you thinking
what I'm thinking?

730
00:29:55.094 --> 00:29:57.629
That two wheels
is better than four.

731
00:29:58.430 --> 00:29:59.999
BRONCO: Okay. sweethearts.
we'll run the full route

732
00:30:00.132 --> 00:30:01.433
to the east evacuation point.

733
00:30:01.567 --> 00:30:02.434
If we need to get her out.

734
00:30:02.568 --> 00:30:03.669
Mom will be transported

735
00:30:03.836 --> 00:30:05.037
on the back of the bike.

736
00:30:05.171 --> 00:30:06.572
(motorbike revving)

737
00:30:09.508 --> 00:30:10.742
(horn blaring)

738
00:30:11.010 --> 00:30:12.644
MORENO: We've got a police car
up ahead.

739
00:30:12.778 --> 00:30:13.779
BRONCO: Who wants to kick 'em
in the ass

740
00:30:13.913 --> 00:30:14.780
and see if they'll kick back?

741
00:30:14.914 --> 00:30:15.814
MORENO: Leave it with me.

742
00:30:15.948 --> 00:30:16.949
BRONCO: Good man. Moreno.

743
00:30:17.083 --> 00:30:18.217
Try not to end up in jail.

744
00:30:18.350 --> 00:30:20.452
(motorbike revving)

745
00:30:20.853 --> 00:30:23.055
- (sirens blaring)
- (shouting in Spanish)

746
00:30:23.489 --> 00:30:25.791
- (motorbike revving)
- (tires screeching)

747
00:30:26.192 --> 00:30:27.493
BRONCO: Head to
the storm drains.

748
00:30:27.759 --> 00:30:29.195
See if they have
the stomach to follow.

749
00:30:29.328 --> 00:30:31.630
- (shouting in Spanish)
- (motorbike revving)

750
00:30:32.664 --> 00:30:33.699
MORENO: This is
too fuckin' easy.

751
00:30:34.867 --> 00:30:36.402
What I need is a pig on a bike.

752
00:30:36.535 --> 00:30:37.904
- (sirens blaring)
- (tires screeching)

753
00:30:38.037 --> 00:30:39.471
(motorbike revving)

754
00:30:44.543 --> 00:30:46.312
SID: Moreno. what the fuck
are you doing?

755
00:30:46.445 --> 00:30:47.880
MORENO: You do your thing.
let me do mine.

756
00:30:49.681 --> 00:30:50.917
BRONCO: Looks like your
dream's come true.

757
00:30:51.217 --> 00:30:52.684
You've picked up a pig
on two wheels.

758
00:30:52.885 --> 00:30:54.887
MORENO: Yep. thank you!

759
00:30:55.021 --> 00:30:56.822
- (motorbike revving)
- (sirens blaring)

760
00:31:01.460 --> 00:31:04.063
You know. surprisingly he's not
completely shit. this guy.

761
00:31:04.363 --> 00:31:06.365
- (motorbike revving)
- (tires screeching)

762
00:31:08.034 --> 00:31:09.401
MORENO: Let's see if this fucker
likes the idea

763
00:31:09.635 --> 00:31:11.003
of dropping twenty foot
into a storm drain.

764
00:31:11.137 --> 00:31:12.538
- (motorbike revving)
- (tires screeching)

765
00:31:16.308 --> 00:31:17.743
(motorbike revving)

766
00:31:17.910 --> 00:31:19.245
(sirens blaring)

767
00:31:19.411 --> 00:31:20.412
(shouting in Spanish)

768
00:31:21.480 --> 00:31:22.314
(motorbike revving)

769
00:31:24.116 --> 00:31:25.517
MORENO: Sadly. he didn't follow.

770
00:31:25.651 --> 00:31:26.652
BRONCO: Coming in beside you.

771
00:31:32.891 --> 00:31:34.260
BRONCO: Turns out
you do actually

772
00:31:34.393 --> 00:31:35.627
have some talents. Moreno.

773
00:31:35.827 --> 00:31:36.862
(dramatic music)

774
00:31:43.669 --> 00:31:45.704
SID: Okay. Looks like
that'll work if we need it to.

775
00:31:45.837 --> 00:31:47.273
MORENO: So. a boat will
pick us up from here?

776
00:31:47.439 --> 00:31:48.574
SID: That's the idea.

777
00:31:48.941 --> 00:31:50.276
But the bikes won't work
if we need

778
00:31:50.409 --> 00:31:51.877
to take someone
who's incapacitated.

779
00:31:52.111 --> 00:31:54.646
For that. we'll need
the ambulance to get us

780
00:31:54.780 --> 00:31:56.315
through town and an ATV
to get us down the storm drain.

781
00:31:56.548 --> 00:31:58.117
Then we get them off on a RIB.

782
00:31:59.085 --> 00:32:00.786
BRONCO: Okay.
so onto the next route.

783
00:32:00.919 --> 00:32:02.488
North evac is a straight shot

784
00:32:02.621 --> 00:32:04.423
through a wind farm
outside the city.

785
00:32:04.556 --> 00:32:07.559
It is our primary extraction
point as our gyrocopters

786
00:32:07.693 --> 00:32:10.062
are the fastest way
to get Rachel off the island.

787
00:32:10.196 --> 00:32:12.431
We'll need to get these
operational and onto the runway

788
00:32:12.564 --> 00:32:14.200
in no more than three minutes.

789
00:32:14.600 --> 00:32:17.403
The only way to do that
is to rehearse.

790
00:32:17.536 --> 00:32:18.804
(blades whirring)

791
00:32:27.613 --> 00:32:29.814
(blades slowing)

792
00:32:29.815 --> 00:32:32.917
(sighs) It takes 25 minutes
to get to the mainland.

793
00:32:32.918 --> 00:32:34.386
Twenty five minutes?

794
00:32:34.753 --> 00:32:36.355
Give me something faster.
I'll get it there quicker.

795
00:32:36.488 --> 00:32:37.723
How long from the hotel?

796
00:32:38.090 --> 00:32:39.191
Got it down to nine
and a half minutes.

797
00:32:39.325 --> 00:32:40.626
Get it down to eight and a half.

798
00:32:40.759 --> 00:32:42.161
That's not possible.

799
00:32:42.394 --> 00:32:43.862
You're right. six and a half
is possible.

800
00:32:43.996 --> 00:32:45.164
SID: This is how we're
gonna do it.

801
00:32:45.297 --> 00:32:46.198
We'll take Rachel
from the hotel.

802
00:32:46.332 --> 00:32:47.433
These have to be out of the shed

803
00:32:47.566 --> 00:32:49.035
and in the air in three minutes.

804
00:32:49.168 --> 00:32:51.803
You two pilot and take Rachel
and me with you.

805
00:32:51.937 --> 00:32:54.940
BRONCO: If this doesn't work.
we go to the west evac.

806
00:32:55.574 --> 00:32:57.276
That means back to the villa.

807
00:32:57.409 --> 00:32:58.477
through the tunnel.

808
00:32:59.178 --> 00:33:01.613
onto the bikes
until it's easier by foot.

809
00:33:01.747 --> 00:33:03.715
Then there's an obstacle.

810
00:33:03.849 --> 00:33:07.353
The upside of the obstacle
is no-one can follow us.

811
00:33:07.519 --> 00:33:10.322
But the downside of
the obstacle is. er...

812
00:33:12.424 --> 00:33:13.192
That's the straightest line?

813
00:33:14.693 --> 00:33:15.627
Fuck off.

814
00:33:16.862 --> 00:33:18.430
I foresee a problem.

815
00:33:18.697 --> 00:33:20.466
Point A. the villa is two
and a half miles that way.

816
00:33:20.599 --> 00:33:21.800
Point B. the west evac point

817
00:33:21.967 --> 00:33:23.635
is seven and a half miles
that way.

818
00:33:23.769 --> 00:33:24.970
This is the straightest line.

819
00:33:27.939 --> 00:33:30.076
Now. I am aware that
there is a 300-foot deep

820
00:33:30.209 --> 00:33:31.877
untraversable ravine before you.

821
00:33:33.212 --> 00:33:35.147
But fortunately.

822
00:33:35.281 --> 00:33:37.649
Baker and I have put a great
deal of thought into this.

823
00:33:37.816 --> 00:33:41.120
And we've discovered that if you
give yourself enough runway.

824
00:33:41.787 --> 00:33:43.289
build up some speed.

825
00:33:43.622 --> 00:33:45.124
and flap your arms like so...

826
00:33:49.961 --> 00:33:52.131
It should take the bump
out of the landing.

827
00:33:54.233 --> 00:33:57.369
Alternatively. there is another
option for the less adventurous.

828
00:33:57.503 --> 00:34:00.372
- (button clicks)
- (line whirring)

829
00:34:01.307 --> 00:34:03.209
- (dramatic music)
- It's. er. called a zipline.

830
00:34:03.409 --> 00:34:04.543
(line whirring)

831
00:34:07.513 --> 00:34:09.781
SID: The zipline takes us
to where our ATVs are hidden.

832
00:34:09.915 --> 00:34:11.517
(motor revving)

833
00:34:12.218 --> 00:34:12.851
BRONCO: Then there's the matter
of getting to the harbour

834
00:34:13.018 --> 00:34:14.686
as quickly as possible.

835
00:34:15.087 --> 00:34:16.855
SID: And like with
the other routes.

836
00:34:17.223 --> 00:34:18.390
we'll need to time
and rehearse this too.

837
00:34:21.059 --> 00:34:21.993
Do it again!

838
00:34:25.931 --> 00:34:27.399
(engine revving)

839
00:34:32.838 --> 00:34:34.273
(motorbike revving)

840
00:34:35.607 --> 00:34:37.376
- (tires screeching)
- (engine idling)

841
00:34:37.909 --> 00:34:39.945
- What happened there?
- I can do better.

842
00:34:40.078 --> 00:34:41.779
- Go on. Fuck off.
- (motorbike revving)

843
00:34:41.780 --> 00:34:43.615
Jesus! Fuck!

844
00:34:44.450 --> 00:34:45.217
Door.

845
00:34:47.353 --> 00:34:48.254
Four minutes.

846
00:34:49.121 --> 00:34:50.356
(rifle fires)

847
00:34:51.690 --> 00:34:52.858
Four feet to the left.

848
00:34:53.125 --> 00:34:54.426
(rifle fires)

849
00:34:55.327 --> 00:34:56.328
MORENO: Three feet to the left.

850
00:34:56.462 --> 00:34:57.996
(chain rattling)

851
00:34:58.130 --> 00:34:59.465
- (rifle fires)
- Two feet to the left.

852
00:34:59.631 --> 00:35:00.799
(mine beeps)

853
00:35:03.869 --> 00:35:04.870
(rifle fires)

854
00:35:07.373 --> 00:35:08.140
Bingo.

855
00:35:11.643 --> 00:35:12.778
(engine revving)

856
00:35:13.912 --> 00:35:15.281
(motorbike revving)

857
00:35:17.115 --> 00:35:17.983
Do it again.

858
00:35:18.116 --> 00:35:18.817
(dramatic music)

859
00:35:20.886 --> 00:35:21.887
Four minutes.

860
00:35:22.120 --> 00:35:23.121
Not too shabby.

861
00:35:23.289 --> 00:35:24.356
Let's go again.

862
00:35:24.656 --> 00:35:26.858
- (gunfire)
- (motorbike revving)

863
00:35:27.226 --> 00:35:28.494
MORENO: Argh. dammit!

864
00:35:32.130 --> 00:35:33.765
2:59. Got it.

865
00:35:33.899 --> 00:35:35.434
- Aaargh!
- (blades whirring)

866
00:35:37.836 --> 00:35:39.905
Three. two. one...

867
00:35:40.172 --> 00:35:41.440
(gun firing)

868
00:35:45.277 --> 00:35:46.345
Not bad.

869
00:35:46.778 --> 00:35:47.813
- (gunfire)
- (motorbikes revving)

870
00:35:53.785 --> 00:35:55.654
In contingency. if the north
evac fails

871
00:35:55.787 --> 00:35:56.822
and we have pursuing vehicles.

872
00:35:56.955 --> 00:35:59.358
we lead them into a banana pie.

873
00:35:59.491 --> 00:36:01.993
There'll be one vehicle
and two bikes.

874
00:36:02.294 --> 00:36:04.463
Bikes will peel off and ram's
horn behind the pursuers.

875
00:36:04.596 --> 00:36:07.299
(motorbikes revving)

876
00:36:07.466 --> 00:36:08.967
You're gonna dig a hole
in the floor.

877
00:36:10.001 --> 00:36:10.902
Question.

878
00:36:11.036 --> 00:36:12.037
What are we digging with?

879
00:36:13.104 --> 00:36:14.139
With your finger.

880
00:36:14.840 --> 00:36:15.907
Or you could use an excavator.

881
00:36:16.041 --> 00:36:17.376
(engine chugging)

882
00:36:18.310 --> 00:36:20.546
BRONCO: You put the crank arm
twenty yards to the right.

883
00:36:20.679 --> 00:36:22.814
Dusty trap doors
to snag enemy traffic.

884
00:36:22.948 --> 00:36:23.682
(pickaxe smashes)

885
00:36:23.849 --> 00:36:24.950
(grunting)

886
00:36:25.317 --> 00:36:26.952
- Aargh...
- BRONCO: We drive over.

887
00:36:27.386 --> 00:36:29.054
I'll jump out and trigger.

888
00:36:29.187 --> 00:36:30.456
(thudding)

889
00:36:31.357 --> 00:36:32.691
We'll lose at least one
down the hole

890
00:36:32.824 --> 00:36:34.326
and then whatever's left.
I'll hose off

891
00:36:34.493 --> 00:36:35.994
with the help of the two bikes.

892
00:36:36.862 --> 00:36:38.897
I'll take Mum and continue
to the west evac.

893
00:36:39.365 --> 00:36:40.732
Did the picture
make things clear?

894
00:36:43.535 --> 00:36:44.670
GROUP: Crystal.

895
00:36:47.072 --> 00:36:48.740
The only time Rachel's
going to be vulnerable

896
00:36:48.874 --> 00:36:50.842
is in transit between the hotel
and the villa.

897
00:36:50.976 --> 00:36:52.844
If she insists on stopping
for ice cream.

898
00:36:53.011 --> 00:36:54.480
we will not be able
to stop her.

899
00:36:54.980 --> 00:36:56.782
So. Gucci. you get the drone up

900
00:36:56.915 --> 00:36:59.251
and everyone else.
invisible but useful.

901
00:36:59.651 --> 00:37:01.086
We do not want them knowing
about the full team

902
00:37:01.253 --> 00:37:02.654
and if they come for a bite.

903
00:37:02.854 --> 00:37:04.890
I want them to lose
their fucking teeth.

904
00:37:05.857 --> 00:37:07.493
We know the evac points.

905
00:37:07.659 --> 00:37:08.960
Speed is our priority.

906
00:37:09.094 --> 00:37:10.362
But because there's
three new routes.

907
00:37:10.529 --> 00:37:12.298
because it is unknown territory.

908
00:37:12.431 --> 00:37:13.932
because it is his island

909
00:37:14.065 --> 00:37:16.001
and because we are outnumbered
ten to one.

910
00:37:16.167 --> 00:37:17.603
we are going to keep rehearsing.

911
00:37:17.769 --> 00:37:18.970
And by rehearse.

912
00:37:19.104 --> 00:37:20.171
he means tick every box.

913
00:37:20.339 --> 00:37:21.273
(engine revving)

914
00:37:21.440 --> 00:37:22.308
Tick every tock.

915
00:37:22.441 --> 00:37:23.275
(motorbike revving)

916
00:37:23.409 --> 00:37:24.209
Lube every wheel.

917
00:37:24.343 --> 00:37:25.110
(brakes screeching)

918
00:37:25.243 --> 00:37:26.512
Lick every stamp.

919
00:37:27.379 --> 00:37:31.417
And steal every inch until
all of those routes are ours.

920
00:37:31.950 --> 00:37:34.786
SID: We need to be one step
ahead of Salazar.

921
00:37:34.920 --> 00:37:36.388
BRONCO: We need to know
his movements.

922
00:37:36.555 --> 00:37:38.390
We need to hear
his conversations.

923
00:37:38.557 --> 00:37:40.826
SID: We need ears
in the penthouse suite.

924
00:37:40.959 --> 00:37:42.561
BRONCO: We can only do this
before he knows

925
00:37:42.694 --> 00:37:44.095
that we're on his island.

926
00:37:44.463 --> 00:37:46.398
Dunne will check out
the access routes.

927
00:37:46.698 --> 00:37:49.468
SID: Moreno and Baker will recce
the hotel's rear exits.

928
00:37:49.701 --> 00:37:51.903
BRONCO: Sidney and I will
casually enter the lobby.

929
00:37:52.037 --> 00:37:53.405
SID: Bronco will have
a heart attack

930
00:37:53.539 --> 00:37:55.541
- to distract the hotel manager.
- (gasping)

931
00:37:56.074 --> 00:37:58.176
BRONCO: She will then kindly
donate her skeleton key.

932
00:37:58.777 --> 00:38:00.479
SID: Bronco will then recover.

933
00:38:00.612 --> 00:38:02.781
- And then Sid will inform her...
- It's low blood sugar.

934
00:38:02.914 --> 00:38:04.350
Just needs a sweetie.

935
00:38:04.816 --> 00:38:05.584
And then my husband and I
will make our way

936
00:38:05.751 --> 00:38:06.852
to the penthouse suite.

937
00:38:07.052 --> 00:38:08.420
Whilst Gucci cuts the cameras.

938
00:38:08.554 --> 00:38:09.488
GUCCI: Cameras are down.

939
00:38:11.923 --> 00:38:13.725
(suspenseful music)

940
00:38:17.829 --> 00:38:18.797
Cameras are off.

941
00:38:25.571 --> 00:38:26.572
(statue clunks)

942
00:38:27.839 --> 00:38:28.840
Shh.

943
00:38:29.408 --> 00:38:30.241
Hear no evil.

944
00:38:34.646 --> 00:38:35.347
Get it in.

945
00:38:37.115 --> 00:38:38.350
I think I know what I'm doing.

946
00:38:51.763 --> 00:38:52.498
Three exits.

947
00:38:53.264 --> 00:38:54.232
Door we came in.

948
00:38:54.366 --> 00:38:55.467
fire escape...

949
00:38:56.301 --> 00:38:58.203
Or over the edge
for a neck breaker.

950
00:38:58.504 --> 00:39:00.305
If anything relevant
is said there.

951
00:39:00.839 --> 00:39:02.408
or if Salazar loses
his patience.

952
00:39:02.541 --> 00:39:03.642
we should know about it

953
00:39:03.875 --> 00:39:05.811
and we get Rachel
off the island.

954
00:39:05.944 --> 00:39:08.580
If they open fire. we fire back
and we do not miss.

955
00:39:08.714 --> 00:39:11.282
If and when Salazar's police
force turn up.

956
00:39:11.517 --> 00:39:12.350
we make them pay.

957
00:39:13.885 --> 00:39:15.220
How exactly do you
wanna handle that?

958
00:39:15.353 --> 00:39:16.588
Oh. you're gonna handle that.

959
00:39:17.456 --> 00:39:19.290
You're gonna plant engine
killers under their cars.

960
00:39:25.196 --> 00:39:27.699
If anyone ends up
in that station.

961
00:39:27.899 --> 00:39:30.769
we need to know how to get them
out of that station.

962
00:39:31.503 --> 00:39:33.639
And if I recall correctly.
it's your turn to take the tour.

963
00:39:35.574 --> 00:39:37.275
(plaza chatter)

964
00:39:37.676 --> 00:39:38.544
Your boys are here.

965
00:39:40.812 --> 00:39:41.847
They look very athletic.

966
00:39:44.249 --> 00:39:45.517
It's only one night.

967
00:39:45.684 --> 00:39:47.486
Don't overdo it.
as you're prone to.

968
00:39:49.888 --> 00:39:50.922
And remember.

969
00:39:51.423 --> 00:39:52.491
I love you.

970
00:39:53.024 --> 00:39:54.593
('La Cucaracha' plays
in background)

971
00:39:56.895 --> 00:39:57.696
Wait for me.

972
00:40:00.231 --> 00:40:01.733
- One more thing...
- Shhh...

973
00:40:03.334 --> 00:40:04.570
Write it in a letter.

974
00:40:05.270 --> 00:40:06.738
But I don't write.

975
00:40:06.872 --> 00:40:08.073
No. not the sombrero.

976
00:40:10.442 --> 00:40:12.077
Oy-oy!

977
00:40:12.744 --> 00:40:13.845
Aah...

978
00:40:14.112 --> 00:40:15.881
La cucaracha...

979
00:40:16.948 --> 00:40:18.617
SID: Sing along with me!

980
00:40:18.750 --> 00:40:20.952
(slurring) La cucaracha
(phone ringing)

981
00:40:21.186 --> 00:40:22.821
La cucaracha...

982
00:40:22.954 --> 00:40:25.056
- RACHEL: Are you ready?
- Yeah. we're ready.

983
00:40:25.190 --> 00:40:27.559
- Is it time?
- Yeah. you should get out here.

984
00:40:27.959 --> 00:40:29.928
Did you get me somewhere
nice to stay?

985
00:40:30.361 --> 00:40:31.797
Oh. it's a marble palace.

986
00:40:32.363 --> 00:40:35.166
Frette sheets and gold shitters.

987
00:40:35.433 --> 00:40:37.068
- Liar.
- Whatever you're gonna be

988
00:40:37.202 --> 00:40:38.970
sleeping in is a hell of a lot
more comfortable

989
00:40:39.104 --> 00:40:40.305
than where Sidney's gonna be
sleeping tonight.

990
00:40:40.472 --> 00:40:41.573
Yo! Hey!

991
00:40:41.740 --> 00:40:43.208
Right now. he's er. pissing

992
00:40:43.374 --> 00:40:45.076
on policeman's boots.

993
00:40:45.611 --> 00:40:46.945
Did you get what you need
from Wolfgang?

994
00:40:47.445 --> 00:40:48.947
It's coming.

995
00:40:49.581 --> 00:40:51.950
I just have one more thing
to do. I'll see you soon.

996
00:40:52.083 --> 00:40:54.820
SID: La cucaracha...
Your turn. ladies!

997
00:40:54.953 --> 00:40:57.923
- La cucarach...
- Hey! Hey!

998
00:40:58.657 --> 00:41:00.258
RACHEL: They're ready.
Let's get him to the island.

999
00:41:02.227 --> 00:41:03.729
Let's make this personal.

1000
00:41:04.362 --> 00:41:05.263
Let's take his toys.

1001
00:41:06.565 --> 00:41:07.866
The jet and the boat.

1002
00:41:08.166 --> 00:41:09.701
He'll be flying to the island
on that jet.

1003
00:41:09.835 --> 00:41:12.538
Oh. he's a clever boy.
He'll find a way.

1004
00:41:12.938 --> 00:41:14.372
Let's go back to court.

1005
00:41:14.673 --> 00:41:16.608
The court approves seizure
of personal assets

1006
00:41:16.742 --> 00:41:18.744
belonging to Manuel Salazar.

1007
00:41:18.910 --> 00:41:20.478
Objection. Your Honor!

1008
00:41:20.646 --> 00:41:21.847
Overruled!

1009
00:41:22.480 --> 00:41:23.515
RACHEL: First. they'll
ground his plane

1010
00:41:23.682 --> 00:41:25.050
under international law.

1011
00:41:25.183 --> 00:41:29.287
Horowitz! I'm standing
outside my jet

1012
00:41:29.420 --> 00:41:33.024
and being told
it no longer belongs to me!

1013
00:41:33.158 --> 00:41:35.627
Y-Yes. of-of course
it's your jet.

1014
00:41:35.794 --> 00:41:37.328
It's just a technical issue.

1015
00:41:37.462 --> 00:41:40.298
Why can't I fly?
It's my fucking jet!

1016
00:41:42.167 --> 00:41:44.636
It's been impounded
under international law.

1017
00:41:44.770 --> 00:41:48.774
Since when did I give a fuck
about international law?

1018
00:41:49.040 --> 00:41:51.476
And there's a-a little more.
You. you...

1019
00:41:51.843 --> 00:41:53.545
I think you might need
to brace yourself.

1020
00:41:53.812 --> 00:41:56.214
And then I'll impound
his boat under maritime law.

1021
00:41:56.347 --> 00:41:59.651
- He won't even let me on board.
- My boat! My fucking boat!

1022
00:41:59.785 --> 00:42:01.119
Now I'll have his attention.

1023
00:42:01.352 --> 00:42:03.054
You don't need to worry.
I am confident

1024
00:42:03.188 --> 00:42:06.324
that we will get them back...
in court.

1025
00:42:06.625 --> 00:42:07.893
SALAZAR: We are not
going to court.

1026
00:42:08.026 --> 00:42:09.628
I want to look her in the eye.

1027
00:42:11.830 --> 00:42:12.964
Set up a meeting on the island.

1028
00:42:16.635 --> 00:42:18.069
- (door clanking)
- Vamos.

1029
00:42:20.839 --> 00:42:22.473
(door creaks. clunks shut)

1030
00:42:24.743 --> 00:42:26.311
- (clipboard clunks)
- (background chatter)

1031
00:42:31.149 --> 00:42:32.050
(handcuffs clunk)

1032
00:42:38.256 --> 00:42:39.424
(door rattles)

1033
00:42:44.362 --> 00:42:45.664
What took you so long?

1034
00:42:46.264 --> 00:42:48.800
I may have overdone it
when I pissed on his boots.

1035
00:42:48.934 --> 00:42:49.668
Got any news?

1036
00:42:52.838 --> 00:42:55.373
I. er... don't belong
to you anymore.

1037
00:42:56.374 --> 00:42:57.475
I don't care about that.

1038
00:42:57.709 --> 00:42:59.077
(suspenseful music)

1039
00:42:59.778 --> 00:43:00.946
Cameras?

1040
00:43:01.847 --> 00:43:03.615
They're connected
but they're unsophisticated.

1041
00:43:04.850 --> 00:43:05.951
Guards?

1042
00:43:06.685 --> 00:43:08.519
Give or take 12
and about 20 across the road.

1043
00:43:09.955 --> 00:43:11.522
- Guns?
- Yeah. Plenty.

1044
00:43:12.691 --> 00:43:13.859
Is there any way in the back?

1045
00:43:14.425 --> 00:43:16.294
Well. you gotta
blow a hole through the wall.

1046
00:43:17.562 --> 00:43:19.698
Next time. you're gonna spend
the night in the cell.

1047
00:43:20.732 --> 00:43:23.568
Nah. you're a soldier.
And you're good with the boys.

1048
00:43:23.702 --> 00:43:26.037
Yeah. you're right.
They'd eat you alive.

1049
00:43:26.404 --> 00:43:28.473
Ooh! On second thought...

1050
00:43:28.640 --> 00:43:30.241
- (suspenseful music)
- (engine starts)

1051
00:43:31.609 --> 00:43:33.111
I picked up their signal
on the way in.

1052
00:43:34.479 --> 00:43:35.380
Abracadabra.

1053
00:43:36.948 --> 00:43:39.017
You've got more tricks
than a clown's pocket

1054
00:43:39.751 --> 00:43:41.452
and you smell
like a wizard's sleeve.

1055
00:43:41.887 --> 00:43:43.621
(suspenseful music)

1056
00:43:45.891 --> 00:43:48.694
Here's our police station.
These are our cells.

1057
00:43:48.827 --> 00:43:50.295
We can't go in the cell wall

1058
00:43:50.428 --> 00:43:52.063
because it's surrounded
by another wall

1059
00:43:52.898 --> 00:43:54.432
and it's covered by cameras.

1060
00:43:54.966 --> 00:43:57.335
So. we have to go inside if we
want to get somebody outside.

1061
00:43:57.468 --> 00:43:58.904
We can go out the back wall.

1062
00:43:59.304 --> 00:44:00.605
It's got no cameras and we can
drive straight up to it.

1063
00:44:00.739 --> 00:44:01.973
- Ah.
- Drone's found

1064
00:44:02.107 --> 00:44:03.274
a nosy visitor. Sir.

1065
00:44:05.844 --> 00:44:08.379
Who do we have here?

1066
00:44:08.847 --> 00:44:11.016
Oh. ten points if you can guess.

1067
00:44:11.182 --> 00:44:12.918
- You gotta give me a clue.
- Big.

1068
00:44:13.084 --> 00:44:14.753
- Elephant.
- Bearded.

1069
00:44:16.654 --> 00:44:18.389
- Bearded elephant?
- Red.

1070
00:44:18.757 --> 00:44:20.058
Red bearded elephant?

1071
00:44:20.358 --> 00:44:22.761
Salazar's head of security.

1072
00:44:27.632 --> 00:44:28.967
Shall we go say hello?

1073
00:44:29.868 --> 00:44:32.037
Nah. I think you're doing
a good enough job.

1074
00:44:32.670 --> 00:44:35.040
SID: Phase three.
Conference with an enemy.

1075
00:44:35.540 --> 00:44:37.308
(dramatic music)

1076
00:44:40.011 --> 00:44:41.212
Majesty.

1077
00:44:41.446 --> 00:44:42.480
Captain Sensible.

1078
00:44:44.883 --> 00:44:46.451
(dramatic music)

1079
00:44:50.655 --> 00:44:51.723
Here. This is for you.

1080
00:44:53.558 --> 00:44:56.194
Oh... this isn't about
to get awkward. is it?

1081
00:44:56.327 --> 00:44:57.195
Just put it on.

1082
00:44:59.731 --> 00:45:01.066
(gasps)

1083
00:45:01.199 --> 00:45:04.669
Sidney... It's beautiful.
Thank you.

1084
00:45:04.803 --> 00:45:05.837
Is there anything in it?

1085
00:45:06.004 --> 00:45:07.338
There's a thing in the thing.

1086
00:45:07.906 --> 00:45:08.974
If you hold down the button.
no matter where you are

1087
00:45:09.140 --> 00:45:10.909
in the world. I'll find you.

1088
00:45:11.542 --> 00:45:13.644
RACHEL: I know when mistakes
are made. you need insurance.

1089
00:45:14.012 --> 00:45:15.446
Bronco and Sid are mine.

1090
00:45:15.580 --> 00:45:16.948
(yells in Thai)

1091
00:45:17.082 --> 00:45:18.316
(bars rattling)

1092
00:45:19.250 --> 00:45:20.952
(cell door creaking)

1093
00:45:21.152 --> 00:45:23.688
With men like these.
you can't buy loyalty.

1094
00:45:23.822 --> 00:45:25.456
It must be earned.

1095
00:45:25.656 --> 00:45:27.793
Don't say a word. Follow me.

1096
00:45:27.926 --> 00:45:29.727
And I earned that
a hundred jobs ago

1097
00:45:29.861 --> 00:45:31.729
when I broke them out
of a prison in Chiang Mai.

1098
00:45:34.665 --> 00:45:36.101
- Are we being followed?
- Yep.

1099
00:45:40.772 --> 00:45:42.373
- Do we care?
- No.

1100
00:45:44.509 --> 00:45:46.544
Is there a reason
why we're driving so slow?

1101
00:45:46.677 --> 00:45:49.147
Dangerous things happen
to people who drive too fast.

1102
00:45:49.280 --> 00:45:50.748
And I wouldn't want them
to get in an accident.

1103
00:45:52.550 --> 00:45:54.119
- (suspenseful music)
- (engine revving)

1104
00:45:54.252 --> 00:45:55.420
(tires screeching)

1105
00:46:07.833 --> 00:46:09.134
- Hello.
- Ma'am.

1106
00:46:12.137 --> 00:46:14.272
- Mr. Beauregard.
- Sir.

1107
00:46:16.074 --> 00:46:20.111
So. marble palace.
Frette sheets. golden shitter?

1108
00:46:20.311 --> 00:46:22.080
Oh no. that's for the kids.

1109
00:46:22.613 --> 00:46:25.150
For you. ma'am.
we have 100% electric RV.

1110
00:46:25.283 --> 00:46:27.352
organic sheets
and a compostable toilet.

1111
00:46:27.585 --> 00:46:28.486
Let me give you a tour.

1112
00:46:29.220 --> 00:46:29.955
Kids.

1113
00:46:31.122 --> 00:46:32.157
Ma'am.

1114
00:46:32.590 --> 00:46:34.125
- (dramatic music)
- (blades whirring)

1115
00:46:41.900 --> 00:46:43.401
(blades whirring)

1116
00:46:52.978 --> 00:46:54.345
(engines humming)

1117
00:46:56.514 --> 00:46:58.183
We start at 350.

1118
00:46:58.349 --> 00:47:00.218
Nudge it to four if we have to.

1119
00:47:00.751 --> 00:47:02.353
- I think you should start...
- (distortion)

1120
00:47:04.589 --> 00:47:06.457
RACHEL: Gucci. any news?

1121
00:47:06.591 --> 00:47:09.160
Ma'am. it sounds like
their final number is 400.

1122
00:47:09.460 --> 00:47:10.361
RACHEL: That's not gonna cut it.

1123
00:47:11.362 --> 00:47:12.931
(engine humming)

1124
00:47:16.868 --> 00:47:18.369
(dramatic music)

1125
00:47:32.884 --> 00:47:34.285
(suspenseful music)

1126
00:47:43.962 --> 00:47:45.530
Señor Salazar. Rachel Wild.

1127
00:47:48.366 --> 00:47:49.567
Miss Wild.

1128
00:47:50.735 --> 00:47:55.140
My client is prepared
to increase the previous offer.

1129
00:47:55.573 --> 00:47:57.242
Well. we're not losing
any time then.

1130
00:47:59.510 --> 00:48:04.115
Mr. Salazar is offering
$350 million

1131
00:48:04.515 --> 00:48:06.317
to wrap this up today.

1132
00:48:06.751 --> 00:48:08.386
Well. I'm prepared
to be here till midnight

1133
00:48:08.553 --> 00:48:10.355
to find a way through
this challenge.

1134
00:48:10.755 --> 00:48:14.993
But. in the spirit of brevity.
throw a sharper dart.

1135
00:48:16.061 --> 00:48:16.827
Four hundred.

1136
00:48:18.429 --> 00:48:20.031
You won't get any more
than that.

1137
00:48:20.165 --> 00:48:21.366
Mr. Salazar. we agreed
to stick to the...

1138
00:48:21.499 --> 00:48:23.868
- Shut up. Horowitz.
- Oh.

1139
00:48:24.002 --> 00:48:26.236
Well. the games begin.

1140
00:48:26.237 --> 00:48:28.739
We move from the tail
to the dog.

1141
00:48:34.779 --> 00:48:38.116
You crossed the line.
Miss Wild. You play dirty.

1142
00:48:39.084 --> 00:48:42.787
For the first time in 15 years
I travelled to this meeting

1143
00:48:42.920 --> 00:48:44.555
in a jet that
didn't belong to me.

1144
00:48:47.858 --> 00:48:52.197
Why? Because someone didn't
respect the rules of the game.

1145
00:48:53.764 --> 00:48:55.633
Someone thought
they were clever.

1146
00:48:56.034 --> 00:48:58.569
But there is a line
separating business wealth

1147
00:48:58.703 --> 00:49:00.271
and personal assets.

1148
00:49:01.039 --> 00:49:03.074
Spencer Goldstein invested
in my business.

1149
00:49:04.042 --> 00:49:05.476
not in my personal space.

1150
00:49:07.112 --> 00:49:10.647
But you have marched an army
across that line.

1151
00:49:10.648 --> 00:49:12.650
Oh... wait.

1152
00:49:15.720 --> 00:49:16.954
I have an image.

1153
00:49:18.056 --> 00:49:20.258
Of a maiden in distress
clutching her pearls.

1154
00:49:20.391 --> 00:49:21.959
I too have an image.

1155
00:49:22.727 --> 00:49:25.596
But I would not be a gentleman
if I shared it with you.

1156
00:49:25.896 --> 00:49:26.964
The debt is a billion dollars.

1157
00:49:27.098 --> 00:49:28.233
I'm just here to help you

1158
00:49:28.399 --> 00:49:29.800
facilitate in any way I can

1159
00:49:29.934 --> 00:49:32.070
you satisfying that obligation.

1160
00:49:32.270 --> 00:49:34.972
I am conscious of the small
print and I don't want you

1161
00:49:35.106 --> 00:49:37.842
to incur surcharges.
penalties. interest.

1162
00:49:39.810 --> 00:49:42.113
I'm also known to be
a rather effective nuisance.

1163
00:49:43.914 --> 00:49:45.350
Your blade has reached its hilt.

1164
00:49:46.351 --> 00:49:47.652
You can't cut any deeper.

1165
00:49:49.520 --> 00:49:51.289
Take what's on the table
and fuck off.

1166
00:49:51.522 --> 00:49:53.091
(dramatic music)

1167
00:50:03.034 --> 00:50:04.969
(suspenseful music)

1168
00:50:08.839 --> 00:50:10.975
RACHEL: Fuck... I need a drink.

1169
00:50:14.845 --> 00:50:15.980
(phone ringing)

1170
00:50:19.317 --> 00:50:20.985
- RACHEL: Glover?
- Boss.

1171
00:50:21.219 --> 00:50:23.821
I need more information.
I can't get him to budge.

1172
00:50:23.954 --> 00:50:26.057
We don't have the leverage
and he knows it.

1173
00:50:26.191 --> 00:50:29.360
GLOVER: (sighs) Look. unless
Wolfgang opens up more files.

1174
00:50:29.494 --> 00:50:30.461
we've bottomed out.

1175
00:50:33.198 --> 00:50:34.132
I want a beer.

1176
00:50:35.633 --> 00:50:36.467
SID: Understood.

1177
00:50:37.635 --> 00:50:39.304
We're making a quick pitstop.

1178
00:50:39.470 --> 00:50:41.272
- DUNNE: What are we doing?
- Boss wants a beer.

1179
00:50:41.406 --> 00:50:43.174
DUNNE: Hell of a time
for a fuckin' beer.

1180
00:50:43.574 --> 00:50:45.710
- Arrivederci. mon amour.
- Don't have too much fun.

1181
00:50:47.078 --> 00:50:48.413
(door shuts. opens)

1182
00:50:49.680 --> 00:50:51.516
SID: Mum and Bronco are heading
into the café.

1183
00:50:51.649 --> 00:50:54.018
Let's secure the perimeter.
Gucci. get the drone up.

1184
00:50:54.752 --> 00:50:55.720
MORENO: Just pulled up.

1185
00:50:58.323 --> 00:50:59.824
DUNNE: Are we all invited
for a beer?

1186
00:51:00.191 --> 00:51:02.193
- SID: Dunne. what's your ETA?
- I'm a minute out.

1187
00:51:02.327 --> 00:51:04.229
BRONCO: Reserved a table
in the back for us.

1188
00:51:04.495 --> 00:51:05.696
How romantic.

1189
00:51:06.531 --> 00:51:07.798
SID: Dunne. on your arrival.

1190
00:51:08.166 --> 00:51:09.134
cover the east side
of the square.

1191
00:51:09.267 --> 00:51:10.735
- Copy.
- Hm...

1192
00:51:12.503 --> 00:51:14.372
Gucci. how we looking?

1193
00:51:14.739 --> 00:51:15.540
Checking now.

1194
00:51:18.243 --> 00:51:20.211
A lot of movement
coming towards the café.

1195
00:51:20.711 --> 00:51:23.214
- Buenas. ¿Qué les ponemos?
- Dos cervezas. por favor.

1196
00:51:23.348 --> 00:51:24.615
Perfecto.

1197
00:51:25.750 --> 00:51:28.686
- BRONCO: How are we doing. Sid?
- Starting to smell a bit fishy.

1198
00:51:31.356 --> 00:51:33.158
DUNNE: See those two muppets
entering the café now?

1199
00:51:33.524 --> 00:51:34.859
They were at Salazar's hotel.

1200
00:51:35.926 --> 00:51:37.562
Bronco. two of Salazar's
guests joining you.

1201
00:51:38.896 --> 00:51:39.564
SID: Do you have them?

1202
00:51:41.732 --> 00:51:43.100
BRONCO: Yeah. got eyes on 'em.

1203
00:51:43.234 --> 00:51:45.370
(suspenseful music)

1204
00:51:46.036 --> 00:51:48.173
Well. this might be more complex
than I thought.

1205
00:51:48.306 --> 00:51:49.840
Well. you like complex.

1206
00:51:50.241 --> 00:51:51.108
GUCCI: Sid. there's two more
entering the bar.

1207
00:51:51.242 --> 00:51:52.410
Okay.

1208
00:51:53.378 --> 00:51:55.613
SID: Bronco. two new customers.
Side door. Bar area.

1209
00:51:55.746 --> 00:51:56.714
Do you have eyes on?

1210
00:51:57.915 --> 00:51:58.649
Eyes on.

1211
00:52:00.585 --> 00:52:02.387
GUCCI: Two more hostiles
outside the bar.

1212
00:52:02.587 --> 00:52:05.089
Bronco. it's getting congested.

1213
00:52:05.390 --> 00:52:07.258
- SID: Baker. you take the bar.
- Baker. you're on.

1214
00:52:07.425 --> 00:52:08.493
I'm bringing the car
to the rear of the café.

1215
00:52:08.659 --> 00:52:09.760
Right.

1216
00:52:09.894 --> 00:52:10.661
SID: Bronco. you're taking her

1217
00:52:10.828 --> 00:52:11.629
out the back door.

1218
00:52:12.830 --> 00:52:14.399
BAKER: Approaching bar entrance.

1219
00:52:14.765 --> 00:52:16.701
- Thank you.
- Just gonna borrow this.

1220
00:52:16.834 --> 00:52:18.403
(bar chatter)

1221
00:52:18.636 --> 00:52:19.470
(clears throat)

1222
00:52:21.239 --> 00:52:23.107
SID: Bronco.
how are we looking in there?

1223
00:52:23.841 --> 00:52:26.143
Yeah. we got two in the lobby.
we've got one in the back bar

1224
00:52:26.277 --> 00:52:27.512
and one in the corridor.

1225
00:52:28.246 --> 00:52:30.414
Do we have a problem?

1226
00:52:30.415 --> 00:52:32.850
Hm... more of a challenge
than a problem.

1227
00:52:34.352 --> 00:52:36.887
Hush puppies on.
we keep this quiet.

1228
00:52:37.021 --> 00:52:38.155
MORENO: Copy.

1229
00:52:39.123 --> 00:52:41.392
Mexico. you've got two bogies
coming from behind you.

1230
00:52:41.526 --> 00:52:42.760
MORENO: I'm on 'em.

1231
00:52:43.027 --> 00:52:45.129
- Eyes on. Guch?
- Two more incoming.

1232
00:52:45.263 --> 00:52:46.897
DUNNE: It's an entire fucking
football team.

1233
00:52:47.031 --> 00:52:48.999
- Dunne. stand by.
- (motorbike revving)

1234
00:52:49.133 --> 00:52:50.501
Anyone else's pants
getting tighter?

1235
00:52:50.635 --> 00:52:51.602
Gucci. sit rep?

1236
00:52:51.769 --> 00:52:52.803
Four sitting out front.

1237
00:52:52.937 --> 00:52:53.938
Four inside.

1238
00:52:54.972 --> 00:52:56.907
Sidney. the back door's
still clear.

1239
00:52:57.708 --> 00:53:00.010
SID: I'll leave the car running
at the back door.

1240
00:53:00.144 --> 00:53:01.546
Entering the rear
of the building.

1241
00:53:01.679 --> 00:53:03.581
GUCCI: Got an Escalade inbound.

1242
00:53:04.382 --> 00:53:06.150
BAKER: There's at least
six on board.

1243
00:53:06.284 --> 00:53:07.985
MORENO: By my count.
that's 14 unfriendlies.

1244
00:53:08.118 --> 00:53:08.919
BRONCO: You set out there?

1245
00:53:09.053 --> 00:53:10.187
Yep. ready when you are.

1246
00:53:12.623 --> 00:53:14.259
SID: They'll be going
for an extraction.

1247
00:53:14.392 --> 00:53:17.194
Moving to the kitchen entrance.
On your command. Bronco.

1248
00:53:17.962 --> 00:53:22.031
Alright. I'm gonna take
the two in the lobby.

1249
00:53:22.032 --> 00:53:23.634
BRONCO: Sid. you take
the back bar.

1250
00:53:24.302 --> 00:53:26.036
Baker. take the corridor.

1251
00:53:26.304 --> 00:53:27.972
(suspenseful music)

1252
00:53:28.306 --> 00:53:29.374
Weapons are free.

1253
00:53:29.640 --> 00:53:30.575
(gun clicks)

1254
00:53:36.247 --> 00:53:38.015
(suspenseful music)

1255
00:53:46.857 --> 00:53:48.459
- (chair scrapes)
- (silencer gunshots)

1256
00:53:48.593 --> 00:53:51.462
- (screaming)
- BRONCO: Two down. Lobby clear.

1257
00:53:51.596 --> 00:53:53.364
- SID: Kitchen clear.
- BAKER: Bar clear.

1258
00:53:54.231 --> 00:53:56.233
- (screaming)
- Let's go.

1259
00:53:56.367 --> 00:53:57.668
BRONCO: Gucci. are we good?

1260
00:53:57.868 --> 00:53:59.537
Bronco. back door's clear. Go.

1261
00:54:00.271 --> 00:54:01.272
GUCCI: They're exiting
the Escalade.

1262
00:54:02.707 --> 00:54:04.275
- DUNNE: Go out the rear.
- (gunshots)

1263
00:54:06.377 --> 00:54:07.545
MORENO: Engaging front entrance.

1264
00:54:08.012 --> 00:54:09.614
- (gunfire)
- (screaming)

1265
00:54:09.747 --> 00:54:10.981
- BAKER: They're down!
- (gunfire)

1266
00:54:11.115 --> 00:54:13.117
SID: Escalade. clear. Baker?

1267
00:54:13.250 --> 00:54:14.352
(gunfire)

1268
00:54:15.353 --> 00:54:16.053
BAKER: Clear.

1269
00:54:18.289 --> 00:54:19.457
BRONCO: Extracting Mom now.

1270
00:54:19.890 --> 00:54:22.191
(screaming. panicking)

1271
00:54:22.192 --> 00:54:23.628
SID: Good shooting.
Let's pack this up.

1272
00:54:24.028 --> 00:54:25.763
(shouting. panicking)

1273
00:54:25.930 --> 00:54:29.133
(dramatic music)

1274
00:54:29.300 --> 00:54:31.235
GUCCI: Bronco. you've got two
on a scooter.

1275
00:54:31.436 --> 00:54:33.103
(scooter revving)

1276
00:54:33.237 --> 00:54:34.939
- (gunshots)
- (crashing)

1277
00:54:35.640 --> 00:54:36.907
(gunshots)

1278
00:54:37.074 --> 00:54:38.275
- Bronco's clear.
- Let's go.

1279
00:54:40.545 --> 00:54:41.646
Get in. Lay down.

1280
00:54:41.812 --> 00:54:43.514
(dramatic music)

1281
00:54:43.648 --> 00:54:45.550
SID: Gucci. let's get
out of here.

1282
00:54:45.716 --> 00:54:46.584
GUCCI: Pulling up.

1283
00:54:49.987 --> 00:54:51.589
Bronco. we good?

1284
00:54:51.989 --> 00:54:54.158
We're good. Mom's secure.
Rendezvous at the villa.

1285
00:54:54.325 --> 00:54:55.860
(engine revving)

1286
00:54:56.260 --> 00:54:57.828
SID: Gucci. back to the villa.

1287
00:54:58.062 --> 00:55:00.164
No wheelspins. no speeding.
don't run any red lights.

1288
00:55:00.297 --> 00:55:02.367
Dunne. if anyone tries to stop
you. shoot them in the face.

1289
00:55:02.733 --> 00:55:05.002
(engines revving)

1290
00:55:09.006 --> 00:55:10.741
(suspenseful music)

1291
00:55:14.311 --> 00:55:15.413
It didn't work.

1292
00:55:17.181 --> 00:55:19.083
W-what didn't work?

1293
00:55:19.984 --> 00:55:20.951
Fourteen men.

1294
00:55:22.286 --> 00:55:24.655
- Fourteen men?
- Fourteen.

1295
00:55:24.789 --> 00:55:25.990
What do you mean.
"fourteen men"?

1296
00:55:29.159 --> 00:55:31.161
Don't tell me you've fallen
into her trap.

1297
00:55:31.529 --> 00:55:33.764
(suspenseful music)

1298
00:55:34.532 --> 00:55:36.200
HOROWITZ: If you tried
to kill her.

1299
00:55:36.333 --> 00:55:38.135
she'll get
an emergency injunction.

1300
00:55:39.970 --> 00:55:41.972
That will turn us upside down.

1301
00:55:44.609 --> 00:55:47.311
Legally. they'll be able
to see everything.

1302
00:55:49.013 --> 00:55:50.848
Get Wolfgang on the phone. now.

1303
00:55:52.783 --> 00:55:54.118
(phone vibrating)

1304
00:55:57.622 --> 00:55:59.123
(phone vibrating)

1305
00:56:05.229 --> 00:56:06.263
GLOVER: Boss?

1306
00:56:06.631 --> 00:56:08.433
Glover. talk to me.

1307
00:56:08.799 --> 00:56:11.702
Wolfgang's moving assets.
Big assets.

1308
00:56:12.236 --> 00:56:13.003
GLOVER: They're panicking.

1309
00:56:13.738 --> 00:56:16.006
(dramatic music)

1310
00:56:16.206 --> 00:56:18.142
I think we've got him.

1311
00:56:18.308 --> 00:56:20.745
Glover. I fucking love you.

1312
00:56:21.145 --> 00:56:23.481
Listen to me. this is what
you're gonna do.

1313
00:56:24.649 --> 00:56:27.017
Connect the assets
to his hidden businesses.

1314
00:56:27.151 --> 00:56:29.420
Attach them to his name
and shut them down.

1315
00:56:29.654 --> 00:56:31.889
We can crack the code
and read the cipher.

1316
00:56:32.256 --> 00:56:34.592
If we cut off his income
streams. he'll have no choice

1317
00:56:34.725 --> 00:56:37.294
but to come back to the table
and pay the full billion.

1318
00:56:37.528 --> 00:56:39.430
If you're all in. we're all in.

1319
00:56:40.965 --> 00:56:43.033
But if you want out.
we can get you out.

1320
00:56:43.834 --> 00:56:44.569
Right now.

1321
00:56:46.103 --> 00:56:47.304
We're staying.

1322
00:56:47.672 --> 00:56:49.740
Sidney. the gift
you gave Wolfgang

1323
00:56:49.874 --> 00:56:51.542
is the gift that kept on giving.

1324
00:56:51.676 --> 00:56:54.378
What started with a drip
ended in a deluge.

1325
00:56:54.612 --> 00:56:58.148
Now I know what Salazar's got
and where he's hiding it.

1326
00:56:58.516 --> 00:57:02.620
And my lawyers are gonna freeze.
seize and bleed him dry.

1327
00:57:02.753 --> 00:57:04.989
The court approves
the application to seek

1328
00:57:05.122 --> 00:57:06.223
international
attachment orders.

1329
00:57:06.356 --> 00:57:07.224
(gavel bangs)

1330
00:57:07.391 --> 00:57:08.993
RACHEL: He'll be fucked.

1331
00:57:09.126 --> 00:57:12.162
Next. Skyecill.
chemical manufacturing.

1332
00:57:12.296 --> 00:57:14.398
Turnover $1.1 billion.

1333
00:57:14.532 --> 00:57:17.301
JUDGE: Look at the evidence.
Mr. Horowitz. It's unambiguous.

1334
00:57:17.434 --> 00:57:19.269
The court approves
the application to seek

1335
00:57:19.403 --> 00:57:21.005
international
attachment orders.

1336
00:57:21.138 --> 00:57:21.939
(gavel bangs)

1337
00:57:22.072 --> 00:57:25.943
(speaking Spanish)

1338
00:57:27.377 --> 00:57:28.946
RACHEL: The panic will set in.

1339
00:57:29.313 --> 00:57:32.016
Primostar Telecom.
His first company.

1340
00:57:32.382 --> 00:57:35.820
$800 million in assets.
His walls will close in.

1341
00:57:35.953 --> 00:57:38.122
A worldwide freezing order
will be put in place

1342
00:57:38.255 --> 00:57:39.289
with immediate effect.

1343
00:57:39.423 --> 00:57:40.591
HOROWITZ: Objection. Your Honor.

1344
00:57:40.725 --> 00:57:42.459
Denied. Motion is granted.

1345
00:57:43.327 --> 00:57:45.029
RACHEL: By now. they'll know
there's a leak.

1346
00:57:45.295 --> 00:57:46.731
JUDGE:
I repeat. the motion to lift

1347
00:57:46.897 --> 00:57:48.699
the corporate veil is granted.

1348
00:57:49.166 --> 00:57:51.736
And finally.
Arkon. digital start-up.

1349
00:57:51.902 --> 00:57:54.304
Cash reserve of $385 million.

1350
00:57:54.438 --> 00:57:56.440
- Freeze...
- (dramatic music)

1351
00:57:56.574 --> 00:57:58.275
- fuck...
- (arguing)

1352
00:57:58.408 --> 00:58:00.310
- ...and seize.
- (padlock clanks)

1353
00:58:00.444 --> 00:58:03.113
The motion to lift the corporate
veil is granted.

1354
00:58:03.247 --> 00:58:04.381
- Objection!
- Denied.

1355
00:58:04.515 --> 00:58:06.050
- Objection. Your Honor!
- Denied!

1356
00:58:06.984 --> 00:58:08.553
RACHEL: It was only a question
of time before they found

1357
00:58:08.686 --> 00:58:09.720
the Trojan rat.

1358
00:58:09.854 --> 00:58:10.955
But by now.

1359
00:58:11.088 --> 00:58:12.256
we have everything I need.

1360
00:58:12.422 --> 00:58:13.758
You have no idea how much this

1361
00:58:13.924 --> 00:58:16.126
is going to cost both of us.

1362
00:58:16.794 --> 00:58:18.829
(suspenseful music)

1363
00:58:24.201 --> 00:58:25.670
(speaking Spanish)

1364
00:58:28.806 --> 00:58:30.174
(phone ringing)

1365
00:58:33.010 --> 00:58:35.713
Horowitz. What do you want?

1366
00:58:36.280 --> 00:58:37.748
My client would like
to see you.

1367
00:58:37.882 --> 00:58:38.649
Now.

1368
00:58:39.483 --> 00:58:41.151
What. now. now?

1369
00:58:41.318 --> 00:58:44.454
Yes. now. now.
That means... now.

1370
00:58:45.790 --> 00:58:46.957
I'll be there when I'm ready.

1371
00:58:49.727 --> 00:58:51.829
(suspenseful music)

1372
00:58:55.566 --> 00:58:58.102
Back into the lion's den.

1373
00:58:58.235 --> 00:59:00.170
Well. thanks to you.
there's less lions.

1374
00:59:06.243 --> 00:59:07.477
(footsteps)

1375
00:59:09.413 --> 00:59:13.050
Miss Wild. I hear there
was a regrettable incident.

1376
00:59:13.217 --> 00:59:15.252
Well. regrettable for some.

1377
00:59:15.385 --> 00:59:17.554
As I'm sure Horowitz
has explained to you.

1378
00:59:17.855 --> 00:59:19.189
Once you try to kill me.

1379
00:59:19.323 --> 00:59:20.324
you've crossed a legal Rubicon

1380
00:59:20.490 --> 00:59:22.126
you can't come back from.

1381
00:59:22.259 --> 00:59:24.394
Now. unless you want me to
choke off the oxygen

1382
00:59:24.528 --> 00:59:28.065
to any more of the ancillary
appendages you possess.

1383
00:59:28.398 --> 00:59:30.334
you'll pay the full ticket
and you'll pay it today.

1384
00:59:32.002 --> 00:59:34.138
You can have 800.

1385
00:59:34.404 --> 00:59:35.706
What the fuck?
I don't want eight.

1386
00:59:35.840 --> 00:59:37.441
I want the full fucking yard!

1387
00:59:37.574 --> 00:59:39.143
And I want my boat
and my jet back.

1388
00:59:39.276 --> 00:59:41.145
Ooh. a billionaire
without his toys.

1389
00:59:41.278 --> 00:59:44.348
An embarrassing paradox!
Get the fuck over it!

1390
00:59:51.188 --> 00:59:54.124
Know when you've won.
Miss Wild. Take the deal.

1391
00:59:54.258 --> 00:59:57.995
No! The deal is you pay
a billion dollars.

1392
00:59:58.128 --> 01:00:00.931
For all your chest banging.
have you recovered

1393
01:00:01.065 --> 01:00:02.432
even a single penny
of the debt?

1394
01:00:03.067 --> 01:00:04.935
No.

1395
01:00:05.069 --> 01:00:07.672
You'll accept the deal.
take the 800

1396
01:00:07.805 --> 01:00:09.339
and return my possessions.

1397
01:00:09.473 --> 01:00:11.575
You know I've seen
behind the curtain.

1398
01:00:11.709 --> 01:00:13.443
You have no more secrets.

1399
01:00:14.244 --> 01:00:16.947
So do you really want me
to resurrect all the bodies

1400
01:00:17.081 --> 01:00:18.182
you've been hiding?

1401
01:00:19.049 --> 01:00:21.251
Because I will let slip
the dogs of administrative war

1402
01:00:21.385 --> 01:00:24.288
and I'll share the exact
location of all those corpses

1403
01:00:24.421 --> 01:00:27.557
with every single investor
you've burned previously.

1404
01:00:29.960 --> 01:00:31.896
And it won't be me coming
for a billion.

1405
01:00:32.062 --> 01:00:33.430
It'll be them coming for five.

1406
01:00:34.331 --> 01:00:36.100
(suspenseful music)

1407
01:00:45.642 --> 01:00:46.476
The billion.

1408
01:00:48.145 --> 01:00:49.747
And you give everything back.

1409
01:00:51.348 --> 01:00:52.349
We're done here.

1410
01:00:52.649 --> 01:00:53.851
(footsteps)

1411
01:01:00.758 --> 01:01:01.658
Pay the bitch.

1412
01:01:04.428 --> 01:01:07.231
Your job was to make sure
nothing like this could happen.

1413
01:01:07.531 --> 01:01:09.033
(ominous music)

1414
01:01:10.467 --> 01:01:12.136
I'm letting you go. William.

1415
01:01:12.703 --> 01:01:14.271
Olsson will take you
to the airport.

1416
01:01:16.440 --> 01:01:18.342
(sinister music)

1417
01:01:18.508 --> 01:01:20.110
(sirens blaring)

1418
01:01:21.045 --> 01:01:22.546
(phone ringing)

1419
01:01:24.214 --> 01:01:26.050
Rachel. How can I help?

1420
01:01:26.183 --> 01:01:27.117
It's done.

1421
01:01:27.284 --> 01:01:28.552
What exactly?

1422
01:01:28.819 --> 01:01:30.554
Salazar's agreed to pay
the full amount.

1423
01:01:32.156 --> 01:01:33.690
That's exactly
what Braxton said.

1424
01:01:33.824 --> 01:01:35.726
Now. there's only two reasons

1425
01:01:35.860 --> 01:01:37.427
why that little red phone
could ring.

1426
01:01:37.561 --> 01:01:39.196
One. you're being fired.

1427
01:01:39.563 --> 01:01:41.265
Two. you're being congratulated
for the brilliant agent

1428
01:01:41.398 --> 01:01:45.269
you hired to help you recoup
your unrecoupable debt.

1429
01:01:45.402 --> 01:01:48.505
If it does. Rachel.
I will be very impressed.

1430
01:01:48.638 --> 01:01:51.575
No. when it does. you'll return
everything we seized.

1431
01:01:51.708 --> 01:01:53.778
Contractually that includes
the jet and the boat.

1432
01:01:53.911 --> 01:01:58.682
- Am I clear?
- Crystal. Consider it done.

1433
01:01:58.816 --> 01:02:03.320
Now. keep looking even harder
at the phone you're looking at.

1434
01:02:05.055 --> 01:02:07.091
Ring. ring.
Mazel-tov. motherfucker.

1435
01:02:10.928 --> 01:02:11.762
(phone snaps shut)

1436
01:02:16.500 --> 01:02:18.102
So. as I was saying...

1437
01:02:18.268 --> 01:02:19.503
(phone ringing)

1438
01:02:21.038 --> 01:02:23.107
- Bobby.
- Mr. Goldstein.

1439
01:02:25.042 --> 01:02:26.043
Congratulations.

1440
01:02:27.444 --> 01:02:28.678
(phone clicks)

1441
01:02:29.013 --> 01:02:30.781
(suspenseful music)

1442
01:02:36.553 --> 01:02:38.122
Bobby. are we really going
to fall out

1443
01:02:38.255 --> 01:02:40.124
over a hundred million?
Call me back.

1444
01:02:40.290 --> 01:02:41.959
(dial tone)

1445
01:02:43.227 --> 01:02:45.762
Getting money out of Salazar
was a stimulating game of chess

1446
01:02:45.930 --> 01:02:47.998
compared to dealing
with Spencer Goldstein.

1447
01:02:48.465 --> 01:02:50.034
You always said
they could never be trusted.

1448
01:02:53.537 --> 01:02:54.905
(water pouring)

1449
01:02:57.942 --> 01:03:00.277
(ominous music)

1450
01:03:00.444 --> 01:03:01.545
Who's that?

1451
01:03:02.079 --> 01:03:03.713
We're a thousand miles
from anywhere.

1452
01:03:04.915 --> 01:03:06.250
- Are we expecting anyone?
- No.

1453
01:03:06.984 --> 01:03:07.818
Rashid?

1454
01:03:09.719 --> 01:03:10.687
Rashid!

1455
01:03:10.921 --> 01:03:12.489
(ominous music)

1456
01:03:13.423 --> 01:03:15.292
Wait there. Rashid?

1457
01:03:21.431 --> 01:03:22.266
Rashid...

1458
01:03:23.834 --> 01:03:25.635
(suspenseful music)

1459
01:03:32.742 --> 01:03:34.611
(dramatic music)

1460
01:03:38.515 --> 01:03:39.316
Shereen!

1461
01:03:43.320 --> 01:03:44.188
Shereen!

1462
01:03:49.326 --> 01:03:50.094
Shereen!

1463
01:04:06.176 --> 01:04:07.777
(wind gusting)

1464
01:04:15.352 --> 01:04:17.321
(engine humming)

1465
01:04:17.454 --> 01:04:18.488
Hello. my lovely.

1466
01:04:22.392 --> 01:04:23.961
(watch ticking)

1467
01:04:24.694 --> 01:04:26.496
(dramatic music)

1468
01:04:48.585 --> 01:04:50.587
(sirens blaring)

1469
01:04:52.923 --> 01:04:54.959
(music playing faintly)

1470
01:04:55.092 --> 01:04:57.094
(treadmill whirring)

1471
01:04:57.394 --> 01:04:59.229
(footsteps)

1472
01:04:59.596 --> 01:05:01.098
(treadmill whirring)

1473
01:05:05.602 --> 01:05:06.603
(fumbling)

1474
01:05:07.671 --> 01:05:08.738
Who the fuck are you?

1475
01:05:09.039 --> 01:05:10.340
- (Bobby gasping)
- (treadmill beeps)

1476
01:05:12.409 --> 01:05:13.610
You can't just walk
into my office!

1477
01:05:14.544 --> 01:05:15.712
Oh yes. we can.

1478
01:05:15.845 --> 01:05:17.948
I've got security cameras.

1479
01:05:18.082 --> 01:05:18.915
There are people watching.

1480
01:05:19.849 --> 01:05:20.750
No. there aren't.

1481
01:05:21.051 --> 01:05:22.519
(Bobby gasping)

1482
01:05:22.786 --> 01:05:23.720
So. who are you?

1483
01:05:26.023 --> 01:05:26.723
What do you want?

1484
01:05:28.525 --> 01:05:29.693
Salazar's taken Rachel.

1485
01:05:31.295 --> 01:05:34.231
Oh... all right.

1486
01:05:35.565 --> 01:05:37.901
You're her boys. I see.
Well. that's kind of sweet.

1487
01:05:40.137 --> 01:05:41.305
It's being handled.

1488
01:05:41.771 --> 01:05:42.806
Everything's being handled.

1489
01:05:44.108 --> 01:05:46.376
How... exactly?

1490
01:05:48.578 --> 01:05:49.779
We're dealing with the Ministry
of Foreign Affairs.

1491
01:05:49.913 --> 01:05:51.115
we're talking to
the State Department.

1492
01:05:51.381 --> 01:05:53.083
we're dealing with
the Spanish police.

1493
01:05:53.250 --> 01:05:55.919
It's a... it's a highly complex
and evolving situation.

1494
01:05:56.053 --> 01:05:57.954
So. you're doing nothing.

1495
01:05:58.088 --> 01:06:01.091
Look. we all just
have to be patient

1496
01:06:01.225 --> 01:06:02.959
and Salazar will
get his toys back.

1497
01:06:03.093 --> 01:06:04.928
Rachel gets released.
She gets paid...

1498
01:06:05.062 --> 01:06:06.263
Whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa.

1499
01:06:06.663 --> 01:06:08.098
(suspenseful music)

1500
01:06:10.000 --> 01:06:12.302
So. you're telling me that
she got you your money back

1501
01:06:12.436 --> 01:06:13.837
and she still
hasn't been paid?

1502
01:06:14.238 --> 01:06:15.405
That's not very nice.

1503
01:06:15.572 --> 01:06:18.242
Look. you stick to the dancing

1504
01:06:19.176 --> 01:06:20.344
and I'll do the thinking.

1505
01:06:20.577 --> 01:06:21.911
Don't be cute.

1506
01:06:22.779 --> 01:06:24.281
Nothing is as simple
as it seems.

1507
01:06:25.182 --> 01:06:26.183
Yes. it is.

1508
01:06:26.416 --> 01:06:28.052
(suspenseful music)

1509
01:06:28.318 --> 01:06:29.119
Pay your debts.

1510
01:06:39.363 --> 01:06:40.597
(door slams)

1511
01:06:48.038 --> 01:06:49.539
(footsteps)

1512
01:06:57.847 --> 01:07:01.818
Miss Wild. we made an agreement.

1513
01:07:02.652 --> 01:07:04.720
I kept my side.

1514
01:07:04.721 --> 01:07:06.656
Spencer Goldstein have not.

1515
01:07:06.790 --> 01:07:08.625
No. it's not that simple.

1516
01:07:09.226 --> 01:07:11.161
They have something
really valuable to me.

1517
01:07:11.561 --> 01:07:13.397
Now I have something
valuable to them.

1518
01:07:15.132 --> 01:07:17.701
